## Chargeback Prevention (Critical)

Visa VAMP program (Jan 2026): "Excessive" threshold at **0.9%** dispute ratio.

Required tools:
- Verifi CDRN (pre-dispute resolution, doesn't count toward VAMP ratio)
- Rapid Dispute Resolution (RDR)
- Clear billing descriptor matching "Navigate Peptides" exactly
- 3D Secure v2 (supported by NMI)

## Integration Architecture

### Option A: WooCommerce-Hosted Checkout (Simplest)
Next.js frontend → Cart API → Redirect to WooCommerce checkout page
- Full AllayPay/NMI plugin compatibility
- All payment gateways work through WooCommerce plugins
- Easiest to maintain

### Option B: Headless Checkout (More Complex)
Next.js frontend → NMI Collect.js tokenization → WooCommerce Store API for order
- Better UX (no redirect)
- Requires NMI JavaScript SDK integration
- Coinbase Commerce via Next.js API routes
- Custom failover logic needed

### Recommended: Start with Option A, migrate to B later.

## Fund Protection
- Separate business bank account for peptide revenue
- 30-day cash reserve for potential processor holds
- Diversify: target 60% card, 25% crypto, 15% ACH
- Budget for 6-10% effective processing cost

## LegitScript

NOT available for RUO vendors. Their October 2025 guidance flags "research chemicals" with RUO disclaimers as red flags. AllayPay works without it.

If business pivots to clinical/telehealth: LegitScript becomes available ($975 app + $2,150/year), unlocks Google Ads, Meta Ads, and better processor terms.
